	WISP using Micro Focus COBOL/2 
	==============================

	Dynamic call "LINK" with parameters

		*$LINKMAIN
		COPY "wisplink.cpy" REPLACING "PROGNAME" BY "SAMPLEX".

	Compiler flags

		-C warning=2		no info messages
		-C "override(NAME) == (XNAME)"	change reserved words
		-x			compile to a.out format
		-xc			compile to .o
		-u			compile to .gnt
		-i 			compile to .int

	Compiling to statically linked executables.

		$ cob -x main.cob suba.cob subb.cob ...  subx.cob \
		>   wispmf.o -lwisp -lilp -lvideo

	Compiling to .int and .gnt format.

		$ cob -xc sample.cob		(sample.o)
		$ cob -i sample.cob		(sample.int)
		$ cob -u sample.cob		(sample.gnt)

		Must use uppercase filenames i.e.   SAMPLE.int

	Making a RTS that includes WISP routines.

		$ cob -xe "" -o wrunmf wrunmf.c wispmf.o -lwtest -lwisp \
		>  -lilp -lvideo

	Runtime considerations.

		COBSW=-F	Allow space in numeric

		wrunconfig	runcbl=wrunmf
				cobol=MF

		COBPATH=.:dir:dir:dir

		Alternate File Status Table  COBSW=+Q

	Running programs

		a.out			$ sample

		.int or .gnt		$ wrun sample
					$ wrun SAMPLE
					$ wrun SAMPLE.int
					$ wrun SAMPLE.gnt


	File list.

		wisplink.cpy		link frontend 
		wispmf.c		MF specific routines
		wrunmf.c		MF RTS with WISP code
		mf.rules		Make rules for MF


